# Railway Environment Variables Template
# Copy these to Railway Dashboard → Variables tab

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# REQUIRED VARIABLES (App won't work without these!)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# JWT Secret Key for authentication (copy from your local .env file)
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-here

# Google Gemini API Key for AI features (get from Google AI Studio)
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key-here


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OPTIONAL VARIABLES
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# PostgreSQL Database Connection (only if using database)
# Railway will auto-create this if you add PostgreSQL service
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:port/database


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# HOW TO ADD THESE TO RAILWAY
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1. Go to: https://railway.app/dashboard
# 2. Click on your service/project
# 3. Click "Variables" tab
# 4. Click "New Variable" button
# 5. For each variable above:
#    - Variable Name: SECRET_KEY (or GEMINI_API_KEY, etc.)
#    - Variable Value: your actual value (without quotes)
# 6. Click "Add" or "Save"
# 7. Railway will automatically redeploy with new variables


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# WHERE TO GET THESE VALUES
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# SECRET_KEY:
# → Open: backend/.env file (in your local project)
# → Copy the value after SECRET_KEY=
# → IMPORTANT: Don't share this publicly!

# GEMINI_API_KEY:
# → Go to: https://ai.google.dev/
# → Click "Get API Key" or "API Keys"
# → Create new API key or copy existing one
# → Paste into Railway

# DATABASE_URL:
# → Option 1: Use Railway's PostgreSQL
#   - Click "New" → "Database" → "PostgreSQL"
#   - Railway auto-creates DATABASE_URL variable
# → Option 2: Use external database
#   - Get connection string from your database provider
#   - Format: postgresql://user:password@host:port/database


